Acute Flaccid Myelitis(AFM): Sudden limb weakness, facial droop, difficulty moving eyes, swallowing problems.
Alpha-gal Syndrome(AGS): Delayed allergic reactions to red meat, characterized by hives, itching, swelling, and digestive upset.
Anaplasmosis: Fever, headache, muscle aches, and malaise, sometimes with a rash.
Anthrax: Skin sores, fever, chills, and shortness of breath, depending on the type of infection.
Avian Flu(bird flu)(avian influenza)(H5N: Flu-like symptoms, such as fever, cough, sore throat, and muscle aches.
Babesiosis: Fever, chills, sweats, headache, body aches, loss of appetite, nausea, and fatigue.
Botulism: Muscle weakness, blurred vision, difficulty swallowing, and difficulty breathing.
Brucellosis: Fever, sweats, chills, weakness, fatigue, headaches, and muscle and joint pain.
Campylobacteriosis: Diarrhea (often bloody), fever, stomach cramps, and vomiting.
Carbapenem-resistant Infection(CRE/CRPA): Varies depending on the site of infection, but can include fever, chills, and localized pain or swelling.
Chikungunya Virus Infection(Chikungunya): Fever, severe joint pain, headache, muscle pain, joint swelling, or rash.
Chlamydia: Often asymptomatic, but can cause painful urination, discharge, and pelvic pain.
Ciguatera(Harmful Algae Blooms): Gastrointestinal, neurological, and cardiovascular symptoms, including nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, tingling, and weakness.
Clostridium Difficile Infection: Watery diarrhea, fever, loss of appetite, nausea, and abdominal pain.
Clostridium Perfringens (Epsilon Toxin): Diarrhea and abdominal cramps, typically lasting less than 24 hours.
Coccidioidomycosis fungal infection (Val: Flu-like symptoms, such as fever, cough, chest pain, and fatigue.  Sometimes a rash.
COVID-19 (sars-cov-2) (VID): Fever, cough, shortness of breath, fatigue, muscle aches, loss of taste or smell.
Creutzfeldt-Jacob Disease (CJD): Rapidly progressive dementia, neurological problems, and personality changes.
Cryptosporidiosis (Crypto): Watery diarrhea, stomach cramps, dehydration, and fever.
Cyclosporiasis: Watery diarrhea, loss of appetite, weight loss, cramping, bloating, increased gas, nausea, fatigue, and low-grade fever.
Dengue Fever: High fever, severe headache, pain behind the eyes, joint pain, muscle and bone pain, rash, and mild bleeding.
Diphtheria: Sore throat, fever, swollen lymph nodes, and a thick coating on the back of the throat.
E. coli: Severe stomach cramps, diarrhea (often bloody), and vomiting.
Eastern Equine Encephalitis (EEE): Fever, headache, chills, and vomiting, which may progress to disorientation, seizures, and coma.
Ebola Hemorrhagic Fever: Fever, muscle pain, headache, sore throat, followed by vomiting, diarrhea, rash, and bleeding.
Ehrlichiosis: Fever, headache, chills, muscle aches, nausea, vomiting, confusion, and rash.
Encephalitis, Arboviral or parainfectiou: Fever, headache, confusion, seizures, and other neurological symptoms.
Enterovirus Infection: Range of symptoms, from mild respiratory illness to severe neurological disease.
Giardiasis (Giardia): Diarrhea, gas, greasy stools that tend to float, stomach or abdominal cramps, upset stomach or nausea, and dehydration.
Gonococcal Infection(Gonorrhea): Often asymptomatic, but can cause painful urination, discharge, and pelvic pain.
Granuloma inguinale: Painless ulcers on the genitals or around the anus.
Haemophilus Influenza disease, Type B (H: Fever, headache, stiff neck, and confusion.
Hantavirus Pulmonary Syndrome (HPS): Fever, fatigue, muscle aches, headaches, dizziness, chills, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and abdominal pain, followed by difficulty breathing.
Hemolytic Uremic Syndrome (HUS): Decreased urination, fatigue, and paleness in the skin.
Hepatitis A(Hep A): Fever, fatigue, loss of appetite, nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, dark urine, clay-colored bowel movements, joint pain, and jaundice.
Hepatitis B(Hep B): Fatigue, poor appetite, stomach pain, nausea, and jaundice.
Hepatitis C(Hep C): Often asymptomatic, but can lead to chronic liver disease.
Hepatitis D(Hep D): Similar to hepatitis B, but can be more severe.
Hepatitis E(Hep E): Fever, fatigue, loss of appetite, nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, jaundice, dark urine, and clay-colored stools.
Herpes: Painful blisters or sores on the genitals, mouth, or other areas of the skin.
Herpes Zoster, zoster VZV (Shingles): Painful rash with blisters on one side of the body.
Histoplasmosis infection (Histoplasmosis: Fever, cough, chest pain, and fatigue.
Human Immunodeficiency Virus/AIDS(HIV/AI: Flu-like symptoms initially, followed by a period of latency, and eventually, opportunistic infections and other complications.
Human Papillomavirus(HPV): Often asymptomatic, but can cause genital warts or certain types of cancer.
Influenza(Flu): Fever, cough, sore throat, muscle aches, and fatigue.
Lead Poisoning: Abdominal pain, constipation, fatigue, irritability, loss of appetite, and developmental delays in children.
Legionellosis(Legionnaires Disease): Cough, shortness of breath, high fever, muscle aches, and headaches.
Leprosy (Hansens Disease): Skin lesions, nerve damage, and muscle weakness.
Leptospirosis: High fever, headache, chills, muscle aches, vomiting, jaundice, red eyes, abdominal pain, diarrhea, and rash.
Listeriosis (Listeria): Fever, muscle aches, and sometimes gastrointestinal symptoms, such as diarrhea.
Lyme Disease: Fever, headache, fatigue, and a characteristic skin rash called erythema migrans.
Lymphogranuloma venereum infection(LGV): Genital ulcers and swollen lymph nodes in the groin.
Measles: Fever, cough, runny nose, red eyes, and a rash.
MelioidosisCDC: Fever, headache, muscle aches, and respiratory symptoms.
Meningitis, Viral: Fever, headache, stiff neck, and sensitivity to light.
Meningococcal Disease, Bacterial(Meningi: Fever, headache, stiff neck, nausea, vomiting, and a rash.
Middle East Respiratory Syndrome Coronav: Fever, cough, shortness of breath, and sometimes gastrointestinal symptoms.
Monkeypox Virus(Mpox): Fever, headache, muscle aches, backache, swollen lymph nodes, chills, exhaustion, and a rash that develops into fluid-filled blisters.
Multisystem Inflammatory Syndrome in Chi: Fever, abdominal pain, vomiting, diarrhea, neck pain, rash, bloodshot eyes, and fatigue.
Mumps: Swollen salivary glands, fever, headache, muscle aches, and fatigue.
Norovirus: Vomiting, diarrhea, nausea, and stomach pain.
Oropouche Virus: Sudden onset of fever, severe headache, chills, muscle aches, and joint pain
Paralytic Shellfish Poisoning (Ciguatera: Tingling and numbness of the mouth, face, and extremities, followed by difficulty breathing and paralysis.
Pediculosis(Lice, Head and Body Lice): Itching and the presence of lice and their eggs (nits) on the hair and skin.
Pelvic Inflammatory Disease(PID): Lower abdominal pain, fever, unusual vaginal discharge, painful urination, and painful intercourse.
Pertussis(Whooping Cough): Severe coughing fits followed by a whooping sound during inhalation.
Plague; Bubonic, Septicemic, Pneumonic (: Swollen lymph nodes (buboes), fever, chills, headache, and weakness.
Pneumococcal Disease (Pneumonia): Fever, cough, shortness of breath, and chest pain.
Poliomyelitis(Polio): Fever, headache, stiff neck, and muscle weakness, which can lead to paralysis in severe cases.
Powassan: Fever, headache, vomiting, weakness, confusion, seizures, memory loss.
Psittacosis(Parrot Fever): Fever, chills, headache, muscle aches, dry cough, pneumonia.
Pthiriasis(Crabs; Pubic Lice Infestation: Itching in the pubic area, small bugs or eggs in pubic hair.
Pustular Rash diseases(Small pox, monkey: Fever, headache, body aches, characteristic rash that develops into fluid-filled blisters.
Q-Fever: High fever, headache, muscle aches, chills, chest pain, pneumonia.
Rabies: Fever, headache, muscle aches, weakness, confusion, agitation, hallucinations, excessive salivation, hydrophobia (fear of water).
Respiratory Syncytial Virus(RSV): Runny nose, cough, fever, wheezing, difficulty breathing.
Ricin Poisoning: Respiratory distress, vomiting, diarrhea, abdominal pain, weakness, seizures.
Rickettsiosis(Rocky Mountain Spotted Fev: High fever, headache, muscle aches, rash that begins on wrists and ankles and spreads to the rest of the body.
Rubella, Including congenital (German Me: Mild fever, rash, swollen lymph nodes. Congenital rubella can cause serious birth defects.
Scabies Infestation(Scabies): Intense itching, especially at night, rash, burrows in the skin.
Scombroid: Flushing, headache, dizziness, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, burning or tingling sensation in the mouth.
Septic Shock(Sepsis): Fever, chills, rapid heart rate, rapid breathing, low blood pressure, confusion.
Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome(SARS): Fever, cough, shortness of breath, pneumonia.
Shigellosis gastroenteritis(Shigella): Diarrhea (often bloody), fever, abdominal cramps, vomiting.
Smallpox: High fever, headache, body aches, characteristic rash that develops into fluid-filled blisters.
Staphyloccal Infection, Methicillin-resi: Skin infections that may look like pimples or boils, redness, swelling, pus.
Staphylococcal Infection, Vancomycin Int: Similar to other staph infections, but less responsive to vancomycin.
Staphylococcal Infection, Vancomycin Res: Similar to other staph infections, but resistant to vancomycin.
Streptococcal Disease, Group A(Group A S: Sore throat, fever, headache, body aches, rash.
Streptococcal Disease, Group B(Strep-B): In newborns: fever, difficulty feeding, lethargy. In adults: urinary tract infections, bloodstream infections, pneumonia.
Streptococcal Toxic-Shock Syndrome, STSS: High fever, rash, low blood pressure, multi-organ failure.
Syphilis, primary, secondary, early late: Primary: painless sore (chancre). Secondary: rash, fever, swollen lymph nodes. Latent: no symptoms. Congenital: birth defects.
Tetanus Infection, tetani(Lock Jaw): Muscle stiffness, spasms, difficulty swallowing, lockjaw.
Trichomoniasis(Trichomonas infection): Vaginal discharge, itching, burning, discomfort during urination.
Trichonosis Infection(Trichinosis): Muscle pain, fever, swelling around the eyes, gastrointestinal symptoms.
Tuberculosis, Mycobacteriosis: Cough (sometimes bloody), fever, night sweats, weight loss, fatigue.
Tularemia(Rabbit fever): Skin ulcer, swollen lymph nodes, fever, chills, headache, muscle aches.
Typhoid Fever, Group D: High fever, headache, abdominal pain, constipation or diarrhea.
Typhus: High fever, headache, rash, muscle aches, confusion.
Vaping-Associated Lung Injury(e-Cigarett: Cough, shortness of breath, chest pain, fever, nausea, vomiting.
Varicella(Chickenpox): Itchy rash with blisters, fever, headache, body aches.
Vibrio cholerae(Cholera): Watery diarrhea, vomiting, muscle cramps, dehydration.
Vibriosis(Vibrio): Watery diarrhea, abdominal cramps, vomiting, fever, chills.
Viral Hemorrhagic Fever(Ebola, Lassa, Ma: Fever, fatigue, muscle aches, headache, vomiting, diarrhea, bleeding.
West Nile Virus: Most people have no symptoms. Some develop fever, headache, body aches, rash, swollen lymph nodes.
Yellow Fever: Fever, chills, headache, muscle aches, nausea, vomiting, jaundice.
Zika Virus Infection(Zika): Fever, rash, joint pain, conjunctivitis. Can cause birth defects in pregnant women.
